The paper deals with a geometric problem of finding the minimum circle containing a set of points in the plane, excluding a given geometric object. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper proposes a data structure to efficiently answer queries of this type, which involves preprocessing the point set. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of finding the minimum circle containing a set of points is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and the study of geometric objects in the plane is also relevant to graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the time complexity of the proposed data structure, which could be classified under theoretical computer science (cs.SC).
